public static void main(String[] args) {
	Display display = new Display();
	Shell shell = new Shell(display);
	Combo c = new Combo(shell, SWT.READ_ONLY);
	c.setBounds(10, 10, 100, 40);
	Button b = new Button(shell, SWT.PUSH);
	b.setText("asdad");
	b.setBounds(10, 60, 100, 40);
	shell.pack();
	shell.open();
	while (!shell.isDisposed()) {
		if (!display.readAndDispatch())
			display.sleep();
	}
	display.dispose();
}

Bug.WithStack:
If you start Eclipse and try to do a commit on a file and there is no commit 
comment history, and you click on the down-arrow in the combo box for 'choose 
a previously entered comment', nothing appears to happen but then you cannot 
click on the Cancel button (it won't get focus at all no matter how many times 
you click on it). If you click on the down-arrow again, then you can click on 
Cancel with no problems. I'm using I20030122.
This is the OS behaviour.

Here is a simple wad to show the problem.  Also happens with SWT.NONE.

public static void main(String[] args) {
	Display display = new Display();
	Shell shell = new Shell(display);
	Combo c = new Combo(shell, SWT.READ_ONLY);
	c.setBounds(10, 10, 100, 40);
	Button b = new Button(shell, SWT.PUSH);
	b.setText("asdad");
	b.setBounds(10, 60, 100, 40);
	shell.pack();
	shell.open();
	while (!shell.isDisposed()) {
		if (!display.readAndDispatch())
			display.sleep();
	}
	display.dispose();
}
I haven't seen it in other Windows applications. Perhaps they add a blank item 
to the combo box or something? If I click on a native app's combo box that 
doesn't have any items in it, I get a small, empty, drop-down box. With the 
combo box in that comment window I get nothing visible happening at all.
I have to mark this WONTFIX.  First of all, it's operating system behavior.  
When a combo box has items, you pull it down and you click somewhere else, 
that click is thrown away so users expect to lose the click.

On my Windows XP box, the combo drops down and shows an empty list.  Not sure 
why yours and VI's is different.  Anyways, I experimented with detecting 
the "empty combo pull down case" and the only way to work around the list 
click is to hide the list.  This isn't a problem on VI's or your machine 
because the list is empty for some reason but on my machine it flashes and 
closes, thus taunting the user - "There might be something interesting in this 
combo box but I'm going to close it quickly for free before you've had a 
chance to read it".

This has to be a WONTFIX.  Sorry.

